  "articleSummary": "The article argues that an AI agent is useless unless it can interact with real business systems, and proposes the Model Context Protocol (MCP) as a universal integration layer that replaces ad‑hoc API wrappers. It explains MCP by analogy to the shift from fragmented USB connectors to a single USB‑C standard, then shows how Mastra’s MCPClient lets developers declaratively register local or remote services (e.g., Google Maps, weather APIs, Wikipedia) and expose them as tools to any agent without writing custom API code. The piece also covers per‑user authentication to avoid shared quotas and data leakage, and demonstrates building composite tools that combine multiple MCP services. The tone is instructional with a light‑hearted “hands‑and‑eyes” metaphor, aimed at developers building production‑grade AI assistants or SaaS platforms.",
